Setting up **Argo CD CLI** (`argocd`) on an **offline VM** requires downloading the binary on a machine with internet, transferring it to the offline VM, and setting it up manually.

---

## ‚úÖ Step-by-Step Guide to Set Up `argocd` CLI on an Offline VM

---

### üß± What You Need

| Item                       | Required? | Notes                            |
| -------------------------- | --------- | -------------------------------- |
| Internet-connected machine | ‚úÖ         | For downloading CLI binary       |
| Offline VM with Linux      | ‚úÖ         | To install and use CLI           |
| SCP, USB, or shared folder | ‚úÖ         | To transfer binary to offline VM |

---

## üßæ STEP 1: Download the Argo CD CLI Binary on an Online Machine

1. Visit the Argo CD GitHub releases:
   üëâ [https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd/releases](https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd/releases)

2. Download the latest Linux CLI binary (e.g., for v2.11.0):

```bash
curl -LO https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd/releases/download/v2.11.0/argocd-linux-amd64
```

3. Rename it to `argocd`:

```bash
mv argocd-linux-amd64 argocd
chmod +x argocd
```

---

## üì¶ STEP 2: Transfer the CLI Binary to Your Offline VM

Choose one of the following:

### Option A: Using `scp` (if VMs can reach each other):

```bash
scp argocd user@offline-vm:/home/user/
```

### Option B: Using USB or Shared Folder

* Copy `argocd` binary to a USB drive or shared folder.
* Mount it on the offline VM.
* Copy the binary into `/usr/local/bin` or another location in your `$PATH`.

---

## üõ†Ô∏è STEP 3: Move and Setup on Offline VM

On your offline VM:

```bash
sudo mv /home/user/argocd /usr/local/bin/argocd
chmod +x /usr/local/bin/argocd
```

Test the CLI:

```bash
argocd version
```

You should see something like:

```
argocd: v2.11.0
  BuildDate: 2024-06-20T10:30:00Z
  GitCommit: abcdef123456
```

---

## üåê STEP 4: Access Argo CD Server on the Offline VM

If your Argo CD is running in the same VM or K8s cluster:

### Port-forward the server:

```bash
kubectl port-forward svc/argocd-server -n argocd 8080:443
```

Then login:

```bash
argocd login localhost:8080 --username admin --password <your-password> --insecure
```

---

## üìã Sample Commands You Can Use

| Command                 | Purpose                  |
| ----------------------- | ------------------------ |
| `argocd login`          | Login to Argo CD server  |
| `argocd app list`       | See list of apps         |
| `argocd app create`     | Create a new application |
| `argocd app sync`       | Trigger sync manually    |
| `argocd app delete`     | Delete an application    |
| `argocd app get <name>` | Get app status/info      |

---

## üîê Optional: Set Bash Autocomplete (Advanced)

```bash
argocd completion bash > ~/.argocd-completion
echo 'source ~/.argocd-completion' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
```

---

## ‚úÖ Summary

| Step | Description                                             |
| ---- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1    | Download `argocd` binary on internet-connected machine  |
| 2    | Transfer binary to offline VM (via USB, SCP, etc.)      |
| 3    | Move to `/usr/local/bin` and set executable permissions |
| 4    | Port-forward or expose Argo CD server                   |
| 5    | Login using CLI and start managing apps                 |

